                <h1>Disable Wallpaper Blur on iPhone: Quick Guide</h1>
                <p>To turn off the wallpaper blur effect on your iPhone, go to Settings > Wallpaper. Select your current wallpaper and tap "Choose a New Wallpaper." From there, choose your desired image. When previewing, ensure "Perspective" is turned off to stop the blur. This keeps your wallpaper looking crisp and clear on your home screen.</p>
